<%# Phase 27 follow-up (2026-05-17) — Bundles modal (formerly Collections
    modal).

    One layout-positioned <dialog> per page render (this partial is
    only emitted when at least one bundle has games — see
    `_bundles_for_shelf.html.erb`). Each bundle tile in the shelf
    points its Stimulus action at this dialog's id; on click the
    `bundles-modal-trigger` controller writes the per-bundle
    games-pane URL onto the inner Turbo Frame's `src` attribute,
    which fetches the games list and swaps it in.

    Closing semantics mirror the project's other layout modals
    (search, IGDB search, notifications):
      - Escape         — native <dialog>.
      - Click outside  — `clickOutside` action.
      - `[close]` link — `close` action on the controller.

    NO JS `confirm()` / `alert()` / `prompt()` (CLAUDE.md hard rule).
%>
<dialog id="bundles-modal"
        class="pane-dialog bundles-modal"
        data-controller="confirm-modal"
        data-action="click->confirm-modal#clickOutside keydown->confirm-modal#keydown">
  <div style="padding: 12px 16px; min-width: 480px; max-width: 900px; max-height: 80vh; overflow-y: auto;">
    <div class="dot-list" style="margin-bottom: 8px;">
      <h2 style="margin: 0;" data-bundles-modal-target="title">bundle</h2>
      <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: "close", href: "#",
                                            data: { action: "click->confirm-modal#close" })) %>
    </div>
    <%= turbo_frame_tag "bundles_modal_frame",
                        src: nil,
                        loading: "lazy",
                        data: { bundles_modal_target: "frame" } %>
  </div>
</dialog>
